      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Hey there! Writing a rejection email is a tricky business, but don't worry, I can help you craft something that's professional, kind, and clear—just like a seasoned senior dev would handle it.\n\nHere's a draft you can use:\n\n---\n\n**Subject:** Update on Your Application for Senior Developer Role\n\nDear [Candidate's Name],\n\nThank you for taking the time to interview with us for the Senior Developer position in Austin. We truly appreciated your technical expertise and the thoughtful insights you shared during the process. Your skills stood out, and we're grateful for the opportunity to have you as part of our team.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we've decided to move forward with another candidate whose experience aligns more closely with our current needs. This was not an easy decision, as we were impressed by your qualifications.\n\nWe wish you the very best in your job search and hope our paths cross again in the future.\n\nWarm regards,  \n[Your Name]  \n[Your Job Title]  \n[Company Name]\n\n---\n\nLet me know if you'd like to tweak the tone or add any specific details!",
