      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. it looks good, but maybe a bit too generic? can we make it a little more personal? like, emphasize that the competition was really tough and that it was a very close call between them and the other person. i don't want them to feel like they just failed a basic test, but that it was just a matter of a very narrow margin.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, you're absolutely right! Making it personal and acknowledging the fierce competition adds a nice touch of respect, especially when the candidate was genuinely strong. It's a bit like telling a fellow adventurer that the other path was just a hair's breadth away from being the chosen one, but the terrain shifted slightly in the end.\n\nHere is a revised version that highlights the close call and the tough competition while keeping it professional and kind:\n\n---\n\n**Subject:** Update on Your Application for Senior Developer Role\n\nDear [Candidate's Name],\n\nThank you again for the time you spent with us for the Senior Developer position in Austin. We were genuinely impressed by your technical depth and the way you navigated our final round. It was a truly competitive process; in fact, the decision was incredibly close between you and the other candidate we selected.\n\nWe felt that your skills were exceptional, but after reviewing the final details of both profiles, we felt the other candidate's specific background aligned slightly better with our immediate project roadmap. It was a tough call, and we truly appreciate the high caliber of talent you brought to the table.\n\nWe are confident you will find a role that matches your expertise even better, and we hope our paths cross again in",
